setWhatIfClockPort(25.10)                            setWhatIfClockPort(25.10)

Name
       setWhatIfClockPort - Defines a port as a clock port

Syntax
        setWhatIfClockPort

       <blackBoxCellName>

       -port <portName>

       Defines a port as a clock port. You can then use the clock port to cre-
       ate  timing  checks  and  sequential timing arcs. Therefore, you can do
       what-if timing analysis without loading the .lib file.

       You can use this command after the module definition of the blackbox or
       the blackblob is available with the I/O's in the Verilog netlist.

Parameters
       <blackBoxCellName>
              Specifies the name of the blackbox or blackblob cell.

       -port <portName>
              Specifies the name of the clock port.

